The Kentucky Wounded or Disabled Veterans Program shall:
Perform outreach to improve wounded or disabled veterans' awareness of eligibility for federal, state, and private wounded or disabled veterans' services and benefits;
Assess the needs of wounded or disabled veterans with respect to benefits and services;
Review programs, research projects, and other initiatives that are or may be:
Designed to address or meet the needs of Kentucky's wounded or disabled veterans; or
Unresponsive or insensitive to the needs of these wounded or disabled veterans;
Recommend changes, revisions, and new initiatives to the commissioner to:
Address deficiencies identified through the review established in paragraph (c) of this subsection; and
Improve benefits and services; and
Incorporate wounded or disabled veterans' issues in strategic planning concerning benefits and services.

The primary components of the program shall be:
Advocacy and Public Awareness. The program shall advocate for wounded or disabled veterans and shall work to increase public awareness about the needs of wounded or disabled veterans. The program shall advocate legislation and policies on the local, state, and national levels to address these issues;
Collaboration. The program shall collaborate with federal, state, and private agencies that provide services to wounded or disabled veterans;
Research and Information Dissemination. The program shall monitor and research issues relating to wounded or disabled veterans and disseminate information and opportunities throughout its network;
Education. The program, through conferences, seminars, and training workshops with federal, state, and private agencies, shall provide guidance and direction to wounded or disabled veterans applying for grants, benefits, or services;
Honor and Recognition. The program shall promote events and activities that recognize and honor wounded or disabled veterans; and
Facilities. The program, through grants and other sources of funding, shall provide facilities as appropriate in support of the program.
